    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Solid, focused fix. Each hunk does one thing: move a side effect out of a retry loop. The `findByRole` replacement eliminates a `let x: Element | null` + non-null assertion pattern, which is a nice TypeScript improvement that falls naturally out of the change. All 16 tests pass.\n\n3 P3, 1 Note. Two of the P3s are about the same test (\"only parameters from latest response\"). The Note questions the PR description's diagnostic framing.\n\nThe PR description says the fix uses `act()` to batch publish calls, but the shipped code publishes bare (the `act()` was correctly removed in commit 2, but the description was never updated). Minor, but a reviewer relying on the description will form the wrong mental model.\n\nPariston's differential diagnosis is worth reading: \"The cleanup is still correct (testing-library recommends calling userEvent outside waitFor), and the fix for the 'only parameters' test addresses a real timing gap. But if these tests remain flaky after this PR, the stated diagnosis won't point to the actual cause, because the stated mechanism was never active.\"\n\n\n---\n\n`site/src/pages/CreateWorkspacePage/CreateWorkspacePage.test.tsx:186`\n\n**P3** [DEREM-2] Two unfixed siblings with the same anti-pattern this PR targets. `publishError` (line 186) and `publishClose` (line 211) both fire inside `waitFor` callbacks, re-triggering `onError`/`onClose` on every retry.\n\nThe `mockPublisher` guard on line 185 (`expect(mockPublisher).toBeDefined()`) is vacuous since the publisher is always defined at line 170. The callback retries because of the assertions on lines 187-191, and each retry re-fires the side effect.\n\n> `mockPublisher.publishError(new Event(\"Connection failed\"));` fires on every `waitFor` retry, re-triggering `onError` and re-updating React state. *(Netero, Mafu-san)*\n\nSame fix pattern as the rest of this PR: move the publish call outside `waitFor`, wrap in `act()` if needed, then assert inside `waitFor`.\n\n> \ud83e\udd16\n\n> \ud83e\udd16 This review was automatically generated with Coder Agents.\n",
